 Rema is presently in conversation with America’s monthly magazine, Rollingstone and in a recently released video on Instastory, the fast-rising Mavin and Jonzing world star revealed some facts about himself and his intention for afrobeats. He revealed that he started making music when he was 7 but didn’t take it seriously until he was 11. His words; I started making music when I was 7 but I got serious with it when I was 11. At that time I was just rapping (and) I went into singing when I was 15. On his plans for afrobeats, Rema said; My plan is to make afrobeats a global language just as hip hop is…I feel it’s actually growing here and from time to time we’ll keep doing our best and (soon) it’ll take a string hold down here in America Speaking on the artistes that influenced his music style, Rema said; I’ll say Lana Delrey, Post Malone, Kid Kudi Watch video;   #Rema drops facts with #Rollingstone  #afrobeats #afrobeattotheworld #music #Notjustok A post shared by  Notjustok.com (@notjustok) on Nov 8, 2019 at 11:30pm PST //www.instagram.com/embed.js    The post VIDEO: “I started Making Music When I Was 7…”- Rema appeared first on Latest Naija Nigerian Music, Songs & Video – Notjustok. Source: NotJust okay